  "text": "Such an encoding can be extremely compact. Suppose the initial state of one PhiloFork is noted (P 0 ). The initial state of a PhiloForkGroup(2) is noted M 2 = (P 0 ) (P 0 ). Then the state of PhiloForkGroup (4) is noted M 4 = (M 2 ) (M 2 ). The state of PhiloForkGroup [CITATION_1] would be M 8 = (M 4 ) (M 4 ), etc... Thus, sharing is extremely high : the initial state of the system for 2 n philosophers only requires 2n + k (k ∈ N) nodes to be represented.",
